# No em dashes or en dashes in user-facing copy

Never use `—` (em dash) or `–` (en dash) in strings shown in the UI, API errors returned to clients, or LLM prompts that shape user-visible titles.

Use instead:
- Two sentences with a period
- A comma
- Hyphen `-` for numeric ranges (e.g. `3-8`, `4-6`)
- The word `to` for ranges when clearer (e.g. `3 to 24`)

Internal code comments and regex that strip dashes from third-party titles are exempt.
